<p>I would perform all my requests to the outside without passing it through my model first. Hey, it worked ¯\_(ツ)_/¯! However, two weeks into bootcamp and I know how to make a 'no page refresh' request without compromising safety. And I also got familiar with best refactoring techniques that will make my code a lot more efficient. Cool! Huh?!</p>

<p>
To wrap it up, learning on my own was great, my passion led me to gain very proximate knowledge of many coding techniques. However, this knowledge can be describe as knowing how to do many things but not knowing how to put it all together – at least the right way. 
</p>
<p>
Bootcamp is providing me with this knowledge that I believe many self-taught developers may not know exists. But is it worth the money? With two weeks in I would say yes but only time (15 weeks) can tell. 
